 1815 |edition=4th |location=Westminster |publisher=A. Constable |url=https://archive.org/stream/waterloocampaig01sibogoog#page/n6/mode/2up}}\n* {{Citation |last=Simms|first=Brendan |year=2014 |title=The Longest Afternoon: The 400 Men Who Decided the Battle of Waterloo |publisher=Allen Lane |isbn=978-0-241-00460-9}}\n* {{Citation |last=Smith |first=Digby |year=1998 |title=The Greenhill Napoleonic Wars Data Book |publisher=London & Pennsylvania: Greenhill Books & Stackpole Books |isbn=978-1-85367-276-7}}\n* {{citation |last=Steele |first=Charles |year=2014 |title=Germany at War: 400 Years of Military History |editor-last=Zabecki |editor-first=David T. |publisher=ABC-CLIO |page=[https://books.google.com/books?id=rCWMBQAAQBAJ&pg=PA178 178]}}\n* {{Citation |last=Summerville |first=Christopher J |year=2007 |title=Who was who at Waterloo: a biography of the battle |publisher=Pearson Education|isbn= 978-0-582-78405-5}}\n* {{Citation |last=Thiers|first=Adolphe |year=1862|title=Histoire du consulat et de l'empire, faisant suite \u00e0 l'Histoire de la r\u00e9volution fran\u00e7aise|location=Paris |publisher=Lheureux et Cie.|url=https://archive.org/details/histoireduconsul20thieuoft|volume=20|language=French}}\n* {{citation |last=Torfs |first=Micha\u00ebl |date=12 March 2015 |url=http://deredactie.be/cm/vrtnieuws.english/News/1.2267618 |title=Belgium withdraws 'controversial' Waterloo coin under French pressure, but has a plan B |work=flandersnews.be}}\n* {{citation |last=Uffindell |first=Andrew |last2=Corum| first2=Michael |year=2002 |title=On The Fields Of Glory: The Battlefields of the 1815 Campaign |publisher=Frontline Books |isbn=978-1-85367-514-0 |pages=[https://books.google.com/books?id=30uaBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA211 211], 232\u2013233}}\n* {{Citation |last=Weller |first=J. |year=1992 |title=Wellington at Waterloo |publisher=London: Greenhill Books |isbn=978-1-85367-109-8}}\n* {{Citation |last=Weller |first=J. |year=2010 |title=Wellington at Waterloo |publisher=Frontline Books 